<dl id="n36209a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36209a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36209a"> 209(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> In Him we trust <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n36209a"><li>FW 550.33 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/lexrB.htm#n36209a">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/l39rB.htm#n36209a">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n36209a">MS BL 47484b-543</ms> </li><li>JJA 59:196 <a name="rBd14" href="../../FF/fdra/rda.htm#rBd14">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/rB/rBd14.htm#n36209a">Draft: III&sect;3B.14</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Atheism.]</font> <font color="green">[Ferguson maintains that &lsquo;Atheism&rsquo;, being so religious-conscious, is a cult itself]</font> &hellip; The &ldquo;Atheists&rdquo; will never recruit from those who are privately Atheists. When a man has learned to keep his religion to himself, he is much too civilised to join the strident chorus of a bunch of puerile &ldquo;damned souls&rdquo; who want to take &ldquo;<mark>In God We Trust</mark>&rdquo; off the coins of our Great Republic. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 435</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
